<plot>Helen Broderick narrates this entry in the series which presents the hobbies of various film personalities; Claire Trevor takes a 16mm camera and uses it to record interesting things she encounters; picture making is also the hobby of Mary Pickford, Charlie Chaplin, Alexander Korda and David O. Selznick, while Jean Parker (who received a film contract by winning a poster contest) and John Beal (a former illustrator) prefer pencil and paper. Bob Burns collects and shelters stray dogs.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?432031</url></doc>
